{
  "stem": "2996.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then were some.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People would try to save people who were socialists, or social democrats, or even communists.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I suppose it was meant-- things have many things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Above all is the fear of the unknown coming to a foreign country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People act differently, speak differently, and so on, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was one of many things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not the most important, the most outstanding impression.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But since you asked that kind of question, that's why I put the stress on that instead of-- collecting stamps, does it mean anything to you?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sure, I collected stamps.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Who doesn't, you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What sort of a Jewish community did you grow up in?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Religious?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Assimilated?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were Orthodox, which is to be expected because of what I told earlier.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We belonged to what was called the Audacious Royal, which was the most impressive Orthodox congregation there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The men would go to the temple with striped pants, a Prince Albert coat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And some of them would come with a high hat, walking, you know, walking to the temple in a high hat.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Others kept their high hats there, somewhere, you know, and changed their derbies, or whatever they wore before that before they went into the thing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But these were the Prussians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "These were the Jews who happened to be Prussian or the Prussians who happened to be Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You could walk in at 10:30, and on a Saturday morning, you could tell before you walked in exactly at what point in the prayers they are.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At one point, they would go upstairs to lift the Torah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I imagine everybody knows what the Torah-- to lift the Torah out and hand it to the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
